5:
This way for healing! Please stand 
single-file; the cleric will be with you 
shortly!
8:
Thank you Liesel, dear. You really are 
an angel!
13:
Thank you for all you do! I don't know 
how I can ever repay you!
15:
There's no need for that, now.
May the Stars keep you safe in their 
embrace.
18:
Man, I almost wish I caught colds more 
often! That felt amazing!
22:
More often?! No!
Promise me you'll eat three meals 
a day and sleep on time!
25:
Papercuts, stubbed toes, sniffles... 
I somehow get the feeling these guys 
don't REALLY need medical attention.
28:
Ahhh... Praise the Stars for lending us 
their sweetest angel!
30:
Oh, you're Robbertson, right? From 
Liesel's fanclub?
33:
I left that name behind me! I've seen 
the Stars' Light, and was born anew—
my baptismal name is Robertson.
37:
Well, it makes a big difference to me! 
I've changed my ways, and YOU could 
stand to change yours! I've the heard 
rumors about your gang.
41:
A big thug of a tiger, a cursed toy 
rabbit that talks, an eerie emotionless 
witch... And a boy who lures people 
into the Kaleidoscope—to spirit them 
away from Palpebra!
42:
Worst of all, I've heard you were 
holding hands with our angel! Grrr, 
I'm so jealous...
45:
Goodness, it sounds like you're the talk 
of the town, Alk!
48:
Liesel, my angel! You didn't really go 
on a date with this guy, did you? All the 
rumors about you walking through the 
bazaar hand-in-hand—they were just 
rumors, right?!
50:
A date?
...Oh, yes, you must mean the time we 
went shopping together!
53:
Look, it wasn't a "date," and Liesel isn't 
YOUR angel, anyways! There are still 
people in line, so scram!
57:
I'm afraid I'm going to have to ask you 
ALL to scram!
60:
Hmph. So YOU were behind this 
unauthorized gathering, Liesel.
63: It's all right, Alk. Let him speak, please.
66:
You're too old to play pretend like this, 
Liesel. You're no doctor, and those 
ruffians aren't real patients.
...You're coming home with me.
71:
Why do insist upon this charity work? 
You've no future as a cleric. The Bishop 
kicked you out of the church—don't 
think I didn't hear about it!
73:
I wasn't "kicked out!" I was sent on an 
important mission to supplement my 
training! Which I will have you know 
I am very much working towards, 
thank you.
75:
A mission? Nonsense! I haven't heard 
anything about a mission.
77: Be-because it's none of your business.
82:
I am your FATHER! Do you have ANY 
idea how worried I've been?!
85:
Too worried! I'm an adult. I can take 
care of myself!
88:
This has nothing to do with your age! 
You'll always be my little girl—and your 
mother's. Lisbel always had a weak 
constitution. Who knows what could 
happen to you?
91:
Nothing! Nothing will happen to me. 
I'm not Mom, I'm me!
96:
Hey, um... I don't mean to interrupt, 
but I promise you Liesel is capable of 
protecting herself.
99:
When I first met her, she knocked out 
three robbers all on her own—and 
healed their injuries afterwards.
104:
Of course! She's got strength, beauty, 
compassion... She's got everything! 
That's what makes her Liesel Berger, 
Angel of the Kaleidoscope!
105:
The Angel of the Kaleidoscope? 
The saint who's rescued countless 
adventurers? No, it can't be... Liesel, 
is that true?
107:
It is, Dad. Please, let me continue 
helping the people! You don't have to 
worry about my health.
109:
With all the progress medicine and 
healing magic have made, the illness 
that plagued Mom isn't as scary as we 
all used to think.
112:
The Stars graced me with their Light—
with the power to help others as the 
Stars helped me!
115:
I want to be a beacon for the lost! 
Hope for the fallen!
118:
*sigh* You sound just like your 
mother. Always putting others first, 
and refusing to listen to a word 
otherwise.
...Do as you wish, Liesel.
123:
However! Allow me at least to say this. 
If you truly wish to help others, this is 
not the place.
127:
Look around you, Liesel. Does this look 
like a poor neighborhood? Do these 
people look lost or desperate? No.
128:
The Stars have blessed this town with 
health and fortune. Go, my dear—
beyond the Stars' embrace, to a place 
that truly needs you.
130:
Oh... You're completely right, Dad.
I—I will.
132:
Good! Hmph, if anything, I'd worry 
about you here with all these rascals 
after you.
134:
You there, boy! Take VERY good care of 
my little girl! If anything harms 
a single hair on her head, Stars help 
you because I WILL come for you!
140: Thank you, Dad. I promise I'll be fine!
